A: You can use the String.split() method to split the string into an array of strings. Then you can use the String.replace() method to remove the "sec" from the end of each string.
String[] split = "1.2 sec 0.4 sec".split(" ");
for (String s : split) {
    System.out.println(s.replace(" sec", ""));
}

Output:
1.2
0.4


